h=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cruizex>CruizeX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 3:05:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No Spells for Evil gnome Enchanters</span><hr size=1> Hello all. I believe I have currently found a screw up by Verant (one of many so to speak) concerning Evil Gnome Enchanters... perhaps even evil gnome wizards, not sure about them though. Anyway, I'm currently level 6 and have been to Ak'Anon, Freeport, and Neriak to buy my spells to no avail. At Ak'anon and Freeport I conned dubiously to guards and merchants so they didn't sell to me, although in the underground of Freeport with the evil class merchants and trainers I did find an evil Human Enchanter who would train me and all merchants conned Indifferent.. but of course all i saw were Necromancer and Shadow Knight spells.. not too much help. In Neriak I conned threateningly to the guards at the front so I didn't even try to go in there. The only way I have received any spells was from a friend who accessed his friends account ( yep, not supposed to do that, but oh well)  which had a good Enchanter on Sullon Zek whom he used to buy a few level 1 and 4 spells for me from the library in Ak'Anon. I have talked to a few people about what could possibly done and have come to the following results:<br>
<br>
Q1: Why don't you do quests in Ak'anon to raise faction so you may shop in the library from the good Enchanter Merchants.<br>
   <br>
A1: No NPC will even give me a quest to raise my faction due to me conning dubiously.<br>
<br>
Q2: Why don't you kill the MoBs that raise faction with Ak'Anon ?<br>
<br>
A2: As I said, I am currently level 6. The MoB's that i know of that contain faction increase for Ak'Anon are much higher level. I can't exactly climb the level charts with my few level 1 spells and 2 level 4 spells. <br>
<br>
Q3: Well why don't you do quests in Freeport to raise faction with them ? Might as well seeing as how that towns almost all evil controlled anyway.<br>
<br>
A3: Glance at A1.<br>
<br>
Q4: You're an Enchanter.. why not use alliance spells or Illusions ?<br>
<br>
A4: Ok, well thats a nice thought... oh yeah, forgot.. I can't buy those spells because of the stated reasons above. <br>
<br>
Q5: ( The most often asked/stated to myself ) Well You shouldn't have been Evil!! .. or.... Well why did you want to be evil.. that was kind of dumb ?<br>
<br>
A5: First off, im a stubborn wank. If I see something extremely hard to accomplish, I don't mind taking on the task... It's a pride thing. If that doesn't suit your tastes then try this: Even if I leave the evil gnome enchantment world alone, hopefully I'll help others who wish to pursue this class/race/deity combination by finding out information for myself. After all .. if it can't be played, then don't make it an option. And for anybody who suggest i just keep using my friends friends account to buy my spells until i can successfully illusion   alliance.. well, my friend won't always be there to do that. I just might have to buy some of my spells on my own one day (gasps in amazement) and I know that not everybody in the world has a friend of a friend who plays a good Enchanter.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well, those are just a few of the questions and ideas I have been asked and told. I would just like to hear from the rest of you as to what I should do... or maybe it is a screw up by Verant. Anyway, sorry if i seem a bit sarcastic... it's just that my nerves are a bit high considering that 14 out of 15 people I talked to suggest that I cast Illsuion   Alliance... lol. Any help appreciated, thanks :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uerolotis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erolotis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 4:01:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Neriak?</span><hr size=1> You can raise your outer guard faction for Neriak by killing assling camps in Nek Forest. That will be able to get you into Neriak and check out the enchanter Guild there.<br>
<br>
I have 2 enchanter friends that are gnomes and have positive faction with Neriak. I have never heard them have problems with buying spells. They even have made the trip to HP to buy the pets and done stien quest.<br>
<br>
If your in game name is here, I will pass it on to one of them and ask them to contact you about helping you out with factions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/umorganti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morganti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 4:29:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Neriak?</span><hr size=1> this problem was known back in test.<br>
as an evil gnomes you con apprhensivly (maybe just a very high dubiously) and merchants WILL deal with you but the second you turn in your guild note your faction drops down low enough with them that they will no longer deal with you,<br>
solution, don't turn in your guild note if you are a<br>
Wizard Enchanter or Magician and evil.<br>
just train and go on killing.  <br>
if you are past the point of no return (5) just have a newbie buy your spells for you or have a friend from a different server create a char there ad buy you spells.  if your &lt; 5 just re-roll. levels 1-4 is about an hour maybe 2 if you work hard. if you are 10ish goto nek and kill some asslings as dude said a min ago and the DE's in the spurned will deal with you.  necs will prolly hate you tho so watch out. <p>"You can take me out back and shoot me but I will be damned if I agree with you."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cruizex>CruizeX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 4:50:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Neriak?</span><hr size=1> ahhh , ok. I'll try both of your advice.. thanks :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 5:39:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Neriak?</span><hr size=1> The Neriak part doesn't sound right.  I know for a fact that agnostic gnomes are able to walk about Neriak freely.<br>
<br>
Also, Gnome Necros following Bertoxx (I assume this is what you picked to be an evil gnome Enchanter) have to get some of their spells from Neriak.<br>
<br>
I would try the Qeynos sewers.  The evil humans of Qeynos also follow Bertoxx, and there are various caster guildmasters down there. <p><H3>Shamoo</H3><br>
<b>Barbarian Warrior of Mithaniel Marr</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ulepin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lepin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 5:53:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> minor illusion</span><hr size=1> Get someone to buy the spell minor illusion for you, move next to merchants, cast minor illusion.  That will make you indifferent faction so you can buy from any of them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uunreal366.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unreal366</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/01 6:14:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: minor illusion</span><hr size=1> Well i am a Iksar monk just had someone invis me and did the whine quest and i am now dubously to the innner and outer neriak guards and i am ally to all merchents. <p>QUZAR
